# Booking Platform Implementation Plan

This document outlines the technical architecture and development plan for building the Hotel & Homestay Booking Platform using the MERN stack.

## User Review Required
- Please review this technical roadmap. Once you approve, we will begin Phase 1 (Frontend & Backend Setup).
- Do you have a preferred Payment Gateway in mind? (e.g., Razorpay, Stripe)
- Would you like the Admin panel to be integrated into the main website, or separated as a different dashboard?

## Proposed Architecture

### Tech Stack
- **Frontend:** React (powered by Vite) + Tailwind CSS + Framer Motion (for smooth modern animations).
- **Backend:** Node.js with Express.js.
- **Database:** MongoDB (using Mongoose for schema modeling).
- **Authentication:** JWT (JSON Web Tokens).
- **Payments:** TBD (Stripe/Razorpay via backend).

### Core Features

#### Customer Facing (The Website)
- **Home Page:** Search bar (Location, Dates, Guests), Featured Hotels & Homestays, Modern Hero Section.
- **Search Results:** Filters (Price, Type, Amenities), Map View (optional), Property Cards.
- **Property Details:** Image gallery, detailed description, amenities, dynamic pricing strictly based on base rate + markup, and booking form.
- **User Dashboard:** View past/upcoming bookings, manage profile.

#### Admin Facing (The Dashboard)
- **Dashboard:** Overview of revenue, total bookings, active properties.
- **Property Management:** Add/Edit/Delete hotels and homestays. Set negotiated Base Price and Platform Selling Price.
- **Booking Management:** View all bookings, statuses, and customer details.

---

## Proposed Changes (Phase 1 Steps)

### Phase 1: Project Initialization & Database Design
- Set up the MERN project scaffolding (Client and Server folders).
- Initialize Tailwind CSS and define the premium modern color palette.
- **MongoDB Schema Design:**
  - `User` Schema (Role: Admin/Customer)
  - `Property` Schema (Type: Hotel/Homestay, BasePrice, SellingPrice, Images, Amenities)
  - `Booking` Schema (UserReference, PropertyReference, Dates, TotalAmount, Status)

### Phase 2: Backend API Development
- `POST /api/auth/register` & `login`
- `GET /api/properties` (with filtering queries)
- `GET /api/properties/:id`
- `POST /api/bookings` (requires auth)
- Admin-only routes for managing inventory.

### Phase 3: Frontend Implementation
- Build `Navbar`, `Footer`, and `Hero` components focusing on premium modern aesthetics.
- Build `PropertyCard` and `SearchFilters`.
- Build the `Booking Checkout Flow`.
- Build the `Admin Dashboard`.

## Verification Plan

### Automated/API Testing
- We will test the REST APIs using a local HTTP client/cURL to ensure endpoints return the correct JSON structure for properties and bookings.
- We will verify JWT authentication flow properly restricts access to Admin routes.

### Manual Verification
- We will run the React frontend locally (`npm run dev`) and test responsiveness on mobile and desktop viewports.
- We will simulate an end-to-end customer booking flow (Search -> View Property -> Checkout -> Success) and an Admin flow (Add Property -> View Booking) to ensure the features work harmoniously.
